{"componentChunkName":"component---src-components-blog-post-js","path":"/wsl-n-php/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h3 id=\"windows-set-up\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#windows-set-up\" aria-label=\"windows set up permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Windows set up</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Search the <code class=\"language-jstext\">windows features</code></li>\n<li>Check a <code class=\"language-jstext\">windows subsystem for Linux</code></li>\n<li>If you want to use <a href=\"https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/wsl/install-win10\">WSL2</a>, just enable a <code class=\"language-jstext\">Virtual machine platform</code></li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"mount-network-drive-in-wsl\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#mount-network-drive-in-wsl\" aria-label=\"mount network drive in wsl permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Mount network drive in WSL</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>To check network drive name (window) : <code class=\"language-jstext\">wmic path win32_mappedlogicaldisk</code></li>\n<li>Mount to WSL : <code class=\"language-jstext\">sudo mount -t drvfs '\\\\[path]\\[path]..' /mnt/[name]</code></li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"set-up-ubuntu\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#set-up-ubuntu\" aria-label=\"set up ubuntu permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Set up Ubuntu</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Version check : <code class=\"language-jstext\">lsb_release -a</code></li>\n<li>Upgrade with remove package if needed : <code class=\"language-jstext\">sudo apt full-upgrade</code></li>\n<li>Count files : <code class=\"language-jstext\">ls | wc -l</code></li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"install-php-apache-laravel\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#install-php-apache-laravel\" aria-label=\"install php apache laravel permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Install PHP, apache, <a href=\"https://laravel.com/docs/7.x/installation\">laravel</a></h3>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-jsbash\"><code class=\"language-jsbash\"><span class=\"token function\">sudo</span> <span class=\"token function\">apt</span> <span class=\"token function\">install</span> <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-y</span> php libapache2-mod-php\r\nphp <span class=\"token parameter variable\">--ini</span>\r\n<span class=\"token function\">sudo</span> <span class=\"token function\">apt</span> <span class=\"token function\">install</span> <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-y</span> <span class=\"token function\">composer</span>\r\n<span class=\"token function\">composer</span> global require laravel/installer\r\n<span class=\"token function\">composer</span> global about</code></pre></div>\n<h3 id=\"start-laravel\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#start-laravel\" aria-label=\"start laravel permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Start laravel</h3>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-jsbash\"><code class=\"language-jsbash\"><span class=\"token function\">composer</span> create-project --prefer-dist laravel/laravel <span class=\"token variable\">$NAME</span>\r\nphp artisan serve</code></pre></div>","frontmatter":{"title":"WSL & PHP","date":"June 11, 2020","spoiler":null}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/wsl-n-php/"}},"staticQueryHashes":["63159454"],"slicesMap":{}}